"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Coinbase shipped an important piece of its wallet product portfolio yesterday, the Coinbase Wallet Browser Extension.\\n\\n> Wallet extension is great for security as your Wallet’s private keys stay on your mobile app, protected by fingerprints, faceID or PIN. [pic.twitter.com/bbg0i7h8zF](https://t.co/bbg0i7h8zF)\\n>\\n> — Coinbase (@coinbase) [May 17, 2021](https://twitter.com/coinbase/status/1394369511906848769?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw)\\n\\nYou can download the chrome extension [here](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/coinbase-wallet-extension/hnfanknocfeofbddgcijnmhnfnkdnaad).\\n\\nIf you want to use DeFi apps, buy and collect NFTs, or do anything that requires a crypto wallet in your browser, then the Coinbase Wallet Extension is the best way to do all of those things.\\n\\nCoinbase Wallet, the mobile app, allows you to sync with your main Coinbase account so that you can hold your crypto at Coinbase and move it to Wallet when you want to transact. I like to think of this like a savings account and a checking account.\\n\\nAnd now all of this is available in the browser.\\n\\nWallets and storing crypto have been too hard for too long. I am excited for Coinbase to make all of this easier and mainstream.\\n\\nDisclosure: I am on the board of Coinbase and am a large shareholder.\\n\",\"timestamp\":1621331430,\"title\":\"The Coinbase Wallet Browser Extension\",\"publication\":\"avc\"},\"digest\":\"GAEAFZxhnwoQEtV34Sw81bwXvHk5X61fegIGf3i5vQk\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xB8332710AB60A1B2e8FE6D775d83524C9E0cE136\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"LTl3aLSRol2QUVUD6CZDmgOh-_8_repOG-vj-b00m1o\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Q21DlwnMAzKTxzvSjREQR-eWtchCVIOEf9pQ8-_jbbs\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"kTRr_2IEeOU9HZCV9n1XI4FYBNeAfYOMeAhFJ4DnAU5g_S_LZ1lPoOl2Yyv1qU7PfiqYZg4KT7YroKXR4uFa0Q\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xa36ed4a1f484cc32e85a01be266ff07df93d7d551959ab6